dwm - dynamic window manager
============================
dwm is an extremely fast, small, and dynamic window manager for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dwm you need the Xlib header files.
JetBrainsMono Nerd Font --> if you don't have it installed make sure to install it or change default font in 'config.h' file.

Font Installation
-----------------
Add JetBrainsMonoNerdFont-Regular.ttf to /usr/share/fonts/ directory. (If it doesn't exist, create it.)

Dwm Installation
------------
cd into dwm directory
run as sudo:

    make clean install


Configuration
-------------
The configuration of dwm is done by creating a custom config.h
and (re)compiling the source code.
